 Hubble-time-integrated SN Ia production efficiency\nthat is several times higher in galaxy clusters than in the field, perhaps\ncaused by a peculiar stellar initial mass function in clusters, or by a higher\nincidence of binaries that will evolve into SNe Ia.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Mar 2018 18:00:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 6 Jun 2018 10:25:05 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 22 Jun 2018 13:43:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-11"}
