 observations, there is ample space for an `ordinary' X-ray-emitting young\nneutron star, born with normal initial spin period, temperature and magnetic\nfield, to be hiding inside the evolving remnant of SN 1987A.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Mar 2018 09:20:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-18"}
